description: Size of the reduced Groebner basis of the ideal < x*y(1)^vj(1)*...*y(n-2)^vj(n-2) - z(j) : j=1,2,...,m >, where vj is the j-th extreme n-breakable vector, m=A141348(n), w.r.t. the degree of x and graded reverse lexicographic ordering of the variables y(1), ..., y(n-2), z(1), ..., z(m).
